-- China shares recoup losses on power producers, carmakers
-- By Grace Li
-- Tue Jul 08, 2014 03:06AM EDT
-- None



HONG KONG, July 8 (Reuters) - China shares ended higher on Tuesday, reversing midday losses as power producers and carmakers outperformed.

The Shanghai Composite Index <.SSEC> ended a choppy session up 0.2 percent at 2,064.02 points. The CSI300 <.CSI300> of the leading Shanghai and Shenzhen A-share listings also gained 0.2 percent. Datang International Power Generation <601991.SS> was a major boost for both indexes, soaring the maximum allowed 10 percent to a 4-month high after it announced a deal to restructure its coal-chemical business. [ID:nH9N0P002E] Its sector rivals also posted solid gains on hopes of stronger electricity demand due to hot weather. Huadian Power <600027.SS> jumped 6.7 percent and Huaneng Power <600011.SS> 2.4 percent.